  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 10 high, 10 medium, 19 normal. Key bases needing attention include Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP); plus 7 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and Iaşi (IAS/LRIA). Network hotspots: Bologna Guglielmo Marconi (BLQ/LIPE), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Ålesund Airport, Vigra (AES/ENAL) and 4 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, thunderstorm / convective risk and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Bologna Guglielmo Marconi (BLQ/LIPE), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 9 others.",
